Running this program will validate the results of the Monty Hall problem by
running through two simulations and calculating the percentage of wins.

The two cases include:
* choosing to switch your picked door
* choosing to keep your original picked door

Output will be similar to:
+-------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                           MONTY HALL PROBLEM                            |
+------------------------------------+------------------------------------+
|              SWITCH                |                 STAY               |
+------------------------------------+------------------------------------+
| * Correct 6683 times.              |   * Correct 3343 times.            |
| * Incorrect 3317 times.            |   * Incorrect 6657 times.          |
| * Probability of winning: 66.83%   |   * Probability of winning: 33.43% |
+------------------------------------+------------------------------------+